# `expo-modules-jsi`'s iOS sources hash differently between developer machines
# and EAS Build's worker. Two distinct contributors: pod install's
# `prepare_command` stamps `Products/` with machine-specific stubs, and the
# enclosing dir hash (tagged `expoAutolinkingIos`) drifts even pre-pod-install.
# Real version changes still flip the fingerprint via package.json + the
# `expoAutolinkingConfig:ios` JSON in `fingerprint.config.js`. Pair this with
# `useRNCoreAutolinkingFromExpo: false` in fingerprint.config.js — without
# both levers `eas build` fails `CONFIGURE_EXPO_UPDATES` with a runtime
# version mismatch on every build.
node_modules/expo-modules-jsi/apple/**
